  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>pepper </strong>and <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>peri peri spice mix</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Mix it all together until well coated and arrange the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> so they are on top of the vegetables (skin side up)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are tender – this is your<strong> one tray spicy roast chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>pineapple</strong> (save the juice!) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Season the<strong> chopped pineapple </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and toss together until fully combined – this is your <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> mayo</strong> and <strong>jerk paste </strong>to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>reserved pineapple juice </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and stir it all together – this your <strong>jerk mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-spicy-chicken-with-pineapple-salsa-and-jerk-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> one tray spicy roast chicken</strong>, drizzle with the <strong>jerk mayo </strong>and top with the <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
